{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859098178,"sessionID":"ses_2868ce04dffefK6oNLwVx9iiF4","part":{"id":"prt_d797353ee0011NdxdbZGa44AvW","messageID":"msg_d79733ffa0016HDjU9hJl4abHP","sessionID":"ses_2868ce04dffefK6oNLwVx9iiF4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7e92c61008b1425094ab6db5ecd46ee8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 实现 Valkey 存储后端，提供高性能的会话持久化能力，支持按过期时间和最后活跃时间索引以便垃圾回收。\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ```\n18: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n19: │                      Application Layer                       │\n20: │                    (Session Manager, GC)                      │\n21: └────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n22:                                    │\n23:                                    v\n24: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                    Store Interface                            │\n26: │  Ping / Get / Store / Update / Delete / List* / Close        │\n27: └────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n28:                                    │\n29:                    ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n30:                    │                               │\n31:                    v                               v\n32: ┌──────────────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────┐\n33: │      redisStore          │    │      valkeyStore         │\n34: │   (go-redis/v9 Client)   │    │   (valkey-go Client)     │\n35: └──────────────────────────┘    └──────────────────────────┘\n36:                    │                               │\n37:                    v                               v\n38: ┌──────────────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────┐\n39: │      Redis Server        │    │      Valkey Server       │\n40: │    (Single/Cluster)      │    │    (Single/Cluster)      │\n41: └──────────────────────────┘    └──────────────────────────┘\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ### Provider Selection\n45: \n46: Singleton `Storage()` reads `STORE_TYPE` env:\n47: - `redis` (default) → `redisStore`\n48: - `valkey` → `valkeyStore`\n49: - Other → init fails, provider remains nil\n50: \n51: ## Data Structures\n52: \n53: ### valkeyStore Struct\n54: \n55: ```go\n56: type valkeyStore struct {\n57:     cli                  valkey.Client\n58:     sessionPrefix        string\n59:     expiryIndexKey       string\n60:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n61: }\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Key Constants\n65: \n66: ```go\n67: const (\n68:     defaultSessionPrefix        = \"session:\"\n69:     defaultExpiryIndexKey       = \"session:expiry\"\n70:     defaultLastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"\n71: )\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### Key Design\n75: \n76: | Key Pattern | Type | Purpose | Score |\n77: |-------------|------|---------|-------|\n78: | `session:{id}` | String | JSON document storing SandboxInfo | - |\n79: | `session:expiry` | ZSET | Index by expiry timestamp | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n80: | `session:last_activity` | ZSET | Index by last activity | `LastActivity.Unix()` |\n81: \n82: ### valkeyClientOption\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: type valkeyClientOption struct {\n86:     InitAddress       []string\n87:     Password          string\n88:     DisableCache      bool\n89:     ForceSingleClient bool\n90: }\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ## API Contracts\n94: \n95: ### Constructor Functions\n96: \n97: #### `newValkeyStore(opts *valkeyClientOption) (Store, error)`\n98: \n99: Creates Valkey client via `valkey.NewClient()` with `ClientOption`:\n100: - `InitAddress`: from opts (comma-split addresses)\n101: - `Password`: from opts\n102: - `DisableCache`: from opts (optional)\n103: - `ForceSingleClient`: from opts (optional)\n104: \n105: Returns `&valkeyStore{cli: client, ...}`.\n106: \n107: #### `newValkeyStoreFromEnv() (Store, error)`\n108: \n109: Environment variables:\n110: \n111: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n112: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n113: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated, split to `InitAddress` |\n114: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n115: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"` |\n116: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | `ParseBool`, sets `DisableCache` |\n117: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | `ParseBool`, sets `ForceSingleClient` |\n118: \n119: ### Store Interface Methods\n120: \n121: #### Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n122: \n123: ```go\n124: func (s *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n125:     resp, err := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()\n126:     if err != nil {\n127:         return fmt.Errorf(\"store: ping failed: %w\", err)\n128:     }\n129:     if resp != \"PONG\" {\n130:         return fmt.Errorf(\"store: unexpected ping response: %s\", resp)\n131:     }\n132:     return nil\n133: }\n134: ```\n135: \n136: #### GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n137: \n138: ```go\n139: func (s *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n140:     if sessionID == \"\" {\n141:         return nil, ErrEmptySessionID\n142:     }\n143: \n144:     key := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n145:     resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build())\n146:     if resp.Error() != nil {\n147:         if valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error()) {\n148:             return nil, ErrNotFound\n149:         }\n150:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: get session %s: %w\", sessionID, resp.Error())\n151:     }\n152: \n153:     data, err := resp.AsBytes()\n154:     if err != nil {\n155:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: read bytes: %w\", err)\n156:     }\n157: \n158:     var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n159:     if err := json.Unmarshal(data, &sandbox); err != nil {\n160:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: unmarshal session %s: %w\", sessionID, err)\n161:     }\n162: \n163:     return &sandbox, nil\n164: }\n165: ```\n166: \n167: #### StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n168: \n169: Validates: non-nil sandbox, non-zero `ExpiresAt`, non-empty `SessionID`.\n170: \n171: Uses `DoMulti` for atomicity:\n172: \n173: ```go\n174: func (s *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n175:     // ... validation ...\n176: \n177:     key := s.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n178:     data, _ := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n179:     \n180:     now := time.Now()\n181:     if sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero() {\n182:         sandbox.LastActivity = now\n183:     }\n184: \n185:     cmds := []valkey.Completed{\n186:         s.cli.B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build(),\n187:         s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Score(float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())).Member(sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n188:         s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Score(float64(sandbox.LastActivity.Unix())).Member(sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n189:     }\n190: \n191:     resp, err := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)\n192:     if err != nil {\n193:         return fmt.Errorf(\"store: multi exec: %w\", err)\n194:     }\n195: \n196:     setnxOK, _ := resp[0].ToString()\n197:     if setnxOK != \"OK\" {\n198:         return ErrSessionExists\n199:     }\n200: \n201:     return nil\n202: }\n203: ```\n204: \n205: #### UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n206: \n207: Updates only the session JSON value, does NOT modify ZSETs.\n208: \n209: ```go\n210: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n211:     // ... validation ...\n212: \n213:     key := s.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n214: \n215:     // Check existence first\n216:     exists := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build())\n217:     if exists.Error() != nil {\n218:         return fmt.Errorf(\"store: check exists: %w\", exists.Error())\n219:     }\n220:     count, _ := exists.AsInt64()\n221:     if count == 0 {\n222:         return ErrNotFound\n223:     }\n224: \n225:     data, _ := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n226:     \n227:     resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build())\n228:     if resp.Error() != nil {\n229:         return fmt.Errorf(\"store: update sandbox: %w\", resp.Error())\n230:     }\n231: \n232:     return nil\n233: }\n234: ```\n235: \n236: #### DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n237: \n238: Atomic cleanup of session key and both ZSETs:\n239: \n240: ```go\n241: func (s *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n242:     if sessionID == \"\" {\n243:         return ErrEmptySessionID\n244:     }\n245: \n246:     key := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n247: \n248:     cmds := []valkey.Completed{\n249:         s.cli.B().Del().Key(key).Build(),\n250:         s.cli.B().Zrem().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n251:         s.cli.B().Zrem().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n252:     }\n253: \n254:     _, err := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)\n255:     if err != nil {\n256:         return fmt.Errorf(\"store: delete sandbox: %w\", err)\n257:     }\n258: \n259:     return nil\n260: }\n261: ```\n262: \n263: #### ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n264: \n265: ```go\n266: func (s *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n267:     if limit <= 0 {\n268:         return nil, nil\n269:     }\n270: \n271:     resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).\n272:         Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).\n273:         Limit(0, limit).Build())\n274: \n275:     if resp.Error() != nil {\n276:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: list expired: %w\", resp.Error())\n277:     }\n278: \n279:     sessionIDs, _ := resp.AsStrSlice()\n280:     if len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n281:         return nil, nil\n282:     }\n283: \n284:     return s.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n285: }\n286: ```\n287: \n288: #### ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n289: \n290: Same pattern as `ListExpiredSandboxes` but uses `lastActivityIndexKey`.\n291: \n292: #### loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n293: \n294: Uses `Mget` for batch retrieval:\n295: \n296: ```go\n297: func (s *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n298:     keys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n299:     for i, id := range sessionIDs {\n300:         keys[i] = s.sessionKey(id)\n301:     }\n302: \n303:     resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build())\n304:     if resp.Error() != nil {\n305:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: mget: %w\", resp.Error())\n306:     }\n307: \n308:     values, _ := resp.AsStrSlice()\n309:     var sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n310:     \n311:     for i, v := range values {\n312:         if v == \"\" { // Missing key, skip\n313:             continue\n314:         }\n315:         var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n316:         if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(v), &sandbox); err != nil {\n317:             continue // Skip unmarshal errors\n318:         }\n319:         sandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n320:     }\n321: \n322:     return sandboxes, nil\n323: }\n324: ```\n325: \n326: Note: Comment states keys should be in same slot (cluster deployment consideration).\n327: \n328: #### UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n329: \n330: ```go\n331: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n332:     if sessionID == \"\" {\n333:         return ErrEmptySessionID\n334:     }\n335: \n336:     key := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n337: \n338:     exists := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build())\n339:     if exists.Error() != nil {\n340:         return fmt.Errorf(\"store: check exists: %w\", exists.Error())\n341:     }\n342:     count, _ := exists.AsInt64()\n343:     if count == 0 {\n344:         return ErrNotFound\n345:     }\n346: \n347:     if at.IsZero() {\n348:         at = time.Now()\n349:     }\n350: \n351:     resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).\n352:         Score(float64(at.Unix())).Member(sessionID).Build())\n353:     if resp.Error() != nil {\n354:         return fmt.Errorf(\"store: update last activity: %w\", resp.Error())\n355:     }\n356: \n357:     return nil\n358: }\n359: ```\n360: \n361: #### Close() error\n362: \n363: ```go\n364: func (s *valkeyStore) Close() error {\n365:     s.cli.Close()\n366:     return nil\n367: }\n368: ```\n369: \n370: ### Helper Functions\n371: \n372: #### sessionKey(sessionID string) string\n373: \n374: ```go\n375: func (s *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n376:     return s.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n377: }\n378: ```\n379: \n380: ## Error Handling\n381: \n382: ### Defined Errors (from store.go)\n383: \n384: | Error | Message | Trigger |\n385: |-------|---------|---------|\n386: | `ErrNotFound` | `store: not found` | Session key absent on GET, or missing on update activity |\n387: | `ErrNilSandbox` | `store: sandbox is nil` | Nil sandbox passed to Store/Update |\n388: | `ErrZeroExpiresAt` | `store: expiresAt is required` | Zero ExpiresAt on StoreSandbox |\n389: | `ErrEmptySessionID` | `store: sessionID is required` | Empty sessionID on any operation |\n390: | `ErrSessionExists` | `store: session already exists` | SETNX returns false (key exists) |\n391: | `ErrPasswordRequired` | `store: password is required` | Empty password when required |\n392: \n393: ### Valkey-specific Error Detection\n394: \n395: ```go\n396: if valkey.IsValkeyNil(err) {\n397:     return ErrNotFound\n398: }\n399: ```\n400: \n401: ## Testing Strategy\n402: \n403: ### Unit Tests\n404: \n405: File: `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n406: \n407: Test categories mirroring Redis tests:\n408: \n409: | Test | Description |\n410: |------|-------------|\n411: | `TestValkeyStore_Ping` | PING → \"PONG\" |\n412: | `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_*` | Success, NotFound, EmptySessionID |\n413: | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_*` | Success, NilSandbox, ZeroExpiresAt, EmptySessionID, Duplicate |\n414: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_*` | Success, NotFound, NilSandbox, EmptySessionID |\n415: | `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID_*` | Success, NotFound, EmptySessionID |\n416: | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_*` | Success, Limit, ZeroLimit, NegativeLimit, SkipMissing, Empty |\n417: | `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_*` | Success, Limit, ZeroLimit |\n418: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_*` | Success, ZeroTime, NotFound, EmptySessionID |\n419: | `TestValkeyStore_Close` | Client close without error |\n420: | `TestValkeyStore_Mget` | Batch load with missing keys |\n421: | `TestNewValkeyStoreFromEnv_*` | Environment parsing validation |\n422: \n423: ### Test Infrastructure\n424: \n425: Use `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` for local Valkey-compatible server:\n426: \n427: ```go\n428: func setupTestValkeyStore(t *testing.T) *valkeyStore {\n429:     mr := miniredis.RunT(t)\n430:     cli, _ := valkey.NewClient(valkey.ClientOption{\n431:         InitAddress: []string{mr.Addr()},\n432:     })\n433:     return &valkeyStore{\n434:         cli:                  cli,\n435:         sessionPrefix:        defaultSessionPrefix,\n436:         expiryIndexKey:       defaultExpiryIndexKey,\n437:         lastActivityIndexKey: defaultLastActivityIndexKey,\n438:     }\n439: }\n440: ```\n441: \n442: ### Integration Tests\n443: \n444: Verify cluster mode compatibility:\n445: - Multi-address `InitAddress`\n446: - Key slot alignment for MGET\n447: - `ForceSingleClient` vs cluster auto-detection\n448: \n449: ## File Structure\n450: \n451: ```\n452: pkg/store/\n453:   store.go              — Interface, errors, constants, singleton (existing)\n454:   store_redis.go        — Redis implementation (existing)\n455:   store_valkey.go       — Valkey implementation (new file)\n456:   store_test.go         — Redis + env tests (existing)\n457:   valkey_test.go        — Valkey-specific tests (new file)\n458:   doc.go                — Package doc (existing)\n459: ```\n460: \n461: ## Dependencies\n462: \n463: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n464: |---------|---------|---------|\n465: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client with builder API |\n466: | `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | latest | Test server |\n467: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | latest | Logging (init error) |\n468: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | local | SandboxInfo struct |\n469: \n470: ## Implementation Notes\n471: \n472: ### Valkey-go Builder Pattern\n473: \n474: Unlike go-redis's method chaining, valkey-go uses builder pattern:\n475: \n476: ```go\n477: // Redis style\n478: s.cli.Get(ctx, key).Result()\n479: \n480: // Valkey style\n481: s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()).ToString()\n482: ```\n483: \n484: ### Multi-command Atomicity\n485: \n486: `DoMulti` executes multiple commands in a single request:\n487: \n488: ```go\n489: cmds := []valkey.Completed{\n490:     s.cli.B().Setnx().Key(k).Value(v).Build(),\n491:     s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(z).Score(s).Member(m).Build(),\n492: }\n493: resp, err := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)\n494: ```\n495: \n496: ### Response Handling\n497: \n498: ```go\n499: resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, cmd)\n500: \n501: // Type conversions\n502: resp.ToString()      // string\n503: resp.AsBytes()       // []byte\n504: resp.AsInt64()       // int64\n505: resp.AsStrSlice()    // []string\n506: \n507: // Error check\n508: resp.Error()\n509: valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error())  // Nil sentinel\n510: ```\n511: \n512: ## References\n513: \n514: - AR-012 — Store interface (existing `store.go`)\n515: - AR-013 — Redis implementation (existing `store_redis.go`)\n516: - valkey-go: https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n517: - Session Store spec: `session-store/spec.md`\n\n(End of file - total 517 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n实现 Valkey 存储后端，提供高性能的会话持久化能力，支持按过期时间和最后活跃时间索引以便垃圾回收。\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Application Layer                       │\n│                    (Session Manager, GC)                      │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/design.md","time":{"start":1775859098145,"end":1775859098176}}}}
