{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859184899,"sessionID":"ses_2868ce04dffefK6oNLwVx9iiF4","part":{"id":"prt_d7974b4d8001FB21B4y7xbyL3t","messageID":"msg_d79739fe1001q6L67cl9rmSjwu","sessionID":"ses_2868ce04dffefK6oNLwVx9iiF4","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-83bec08b2078413bb3865054c773bcdf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","content":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Dependencies Setup\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Add valkey-go dependency\n  - Run: `go get github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go@latest`\n  - Verify: `go mod tidy && cat go.mod | grep valkey-go`\n  - Independently verifiable: Dependency appears in go.mod\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Verify miniredis for testing\n  - Check: `cat go.mod | grep miniredis` (already present)\n  - Independently verifiable: Dependency confirmed\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Create valkeyStore Struct and Constructor\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` with struct definition\n  - Define `valkeyStore struct` with `cli valkey.Client` field\n  - Add key constants: `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`\n  - Add `sessionKey(sessionID string) string` helper\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: File compiles without error\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Implement `newValkeyStore(opts *valkeyClientOption) (Store, error)`\n  - Use `valkey.NewClient(valkey.ClientOption{})`\n  - Set `InitAddress`, `Password`, `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient`\n  - Return initialized `valkeyStore`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Constructor compiles\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Update `newValkeyStoreFromEnv()` in `store_redis.go`\n  - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated → split to InitAddress)\n  - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`\n  - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool)\n  - Call `newValkeyStore(opts)`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Env parsing compiles\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Implement Store Interface Methods\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n  - Use `s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()`\n  - Check response == \"PONG\"\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Validate empty sessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - Use `s.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()`\n  - Detect `valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error())` → `ErrNotFound`\n  - JSON unmarshal → `types.SandboxInfo`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n  - Validate: nil sandbox, zero ExpiresAt, empty SessionID\n  - Use `DoMulti` for atomicity:\n    - `Setnx` for session key\n    - `Zadd` for expiryIndexKey\n    - `Zadd` for lastActivityIndexKey\n  - Check SETNX result → `ErrSessionExists` if not \"OK\"\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.4** Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n  - Validate: nil sandbox, empty SessionID\n  - Check existence via `Exists()` → `ErrNotFound`\n  - Use `Set()` to update JSON value\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.5** Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error`\n  - Validate empty sessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - Use `DoMulti` for atomic cleanup:\n    - `Del` session key\n    - `Zrem` from expiryIndexKey\n    - `Zrem` from lastActivityIndexKey\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.6** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Return `nil` if limit <= 0\n  - Use `Zrangebyscore().Min(\"-inf\").Max(timestamp).Limit(0, limit)`\n  - Call `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` for batch retrieval\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.7** Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Same pattern as T3.6 but uses `lastActivityIndexKey`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.8** Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Build keys from sessionIDs\n  - Use `Mget()` for batch retrieval\n  - Skip missing keys (empty string)\n  - Skip unmarshal errors (continue)\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.9** Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error`\n  - Validate empty sessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - Check existence → `ErrNotFound`\n  - Default `at` to `time.Now()` if zero\n  - Use `Zadd()` to update score in lastActivityIndexKey\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.10** Implement `Close() error`\n  - Call `s.cli.Close()`\n  - Return nil\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: Remove Stub Implementation\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Remove stub valkeyStore from `store_redis.go`\n  - Delete lines 384-439 (stub struct and methods)\n  - Keep `valkeyClientOption` struct and `newValkeyStoreFromEnv` logic\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Build succeeds\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: Unit Tests\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` with test helper\n  - Implement `setupTestValkeyStore(t) *valkeyStore`\n  - Use `miniredis.RunT(t)` as test server\n  - Create `valkey.NewClient()` connecting to miniredis\n  - Independently verifiable: Test helper compiles\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Test `Ping` success\n  - Verify `Ping()` returns no error\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Test `GetSandboxBySessionID` scenarios\n  - Success: pre-populate key, verify retrieval\n  - NotFound: query missing key → `ErrNotFound`\n  - EmptySessionID: empty input → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - Independently verifiable: All 3 tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Test `StoreSandbox` scenarios\n  - Success: verify key + both ZSET entries\n  - NilSandbox → `ErrNilSandbox`\n  - ZeroExpiresAt → `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n  - EmptySessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - Duplicate → `ErrSessionExists`\n  - Independently verifiable: All 5 tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T5.5** Test `UpdateSandbox` scenarios\n  - Success: store first, update, verify new value\n  - NotFound → `ErrNotFound`\n  - NilSandbox → `ErrNilSandbox`\n  - EmptySessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - Independently verifiable: All 4 tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T5.6** Test `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` scenarios\n  - Success: verify key + ZSETs removed\n  - NotFound: no error (idempotent)\n  - EmptySessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - Independently verifiable: All 3 tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T5.7** Test `ListExpiredSandboxes` scenarios\n  - Success: expired vs active separation\n  - Limit: respect limit parameter\n  - ZeroLimit: return nil\n  - NegativeLimit: return nil\n  - SkipMissing: orphan ZSET entry skipped\n  - Empty: return nil when no expired\n  - Independently verifiable: All 6 tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T5.8** Test `ListInactiveSandboxes` scenarios\n  - Success: inactive vs active separation\n  - Limit: respect limit parameter\n  - ZeroLimit: return nil\n  - Empty: return nil when no inactive\n  - Independently verifiable: All 4 tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T5.9** Test `UpdateSessionLastActivity` scenarios\n  - Success: verify ZSET score updated\n  - ZeroTime: defaults to `time.Now()`\n  - NotFound → `ErrNotFound`\n  - EmptySessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - Independently verifiable: All 4 tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T5.10** Test `Close` and `Mget` batch load\n  - Close: verify client closes without error\n  - Mget: batch load with missing keys skipped\n  - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T5.11** Test `newValkeyStoreFromEnv` scenarios\n  - Missing ADDR → error\n  - Missing password (required) → `ErrPasswordRequired`\n  - Password not required → success\n  - DisableCache / ForceSingle parsed correctly\n  - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Phase 6: Validation and Integration\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Run `go vet ./pkg/store/...`\n  - Verify: No warnings\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/store/...`\n  - Verify: No errors\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Run all tests with race detector\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/store/... -race -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: All tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/store/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n  - Run: `go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total`\n  - Independently verifiable: Coverage ≥ 80%\n\n- [ ] **T6.5** Verify integration with `Storage()` singleton\n  - Set `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n  - Call `Storage()` → returns valkeyStore\n  - Verify Ping works\n  - Independently verifiable: Integration test passes\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] valkeyStore 完整实现 Store 接口 (all 10 methods)\n- [ ] 支持 5 个环境变量配置\n- [ ] ZSET 索引正确维护 (expiry + last_activity)\n- [ ] 错误处理完善 (6 种错误类型)\n- [ ] Pass `go vet`\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint`\n- [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n- [ ] Integration with Storage() singleton works\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Lines Changed |\n|------|--------|---------------|\n| `go.mod` | Modify | +1 (valkey-go dependency) |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Create | ~200 lines |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Modify | -60 lines (stub removal) |\n| `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` | Create | ~150 lines |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- valkey-go Builder pattern: `s.cli.B().Get().Key(k).Build()`\n- Atomic multi-command: `s.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n- Nil detection: `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)`\n- Response types: `ToString()`, `AsBytes()`, `AsInt64()`, `AsStrSlice()`\n- miniredis compatible with Valkey protocol"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/store/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":242,"character":20},"end":{"line":242,"character":39}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/deprecated"},"source":"deprecated","message":"s.cli.ZRangeByScore is deprecated: Use ZRangeArgs with ByScore option instead as of Redis 6.2.0.","tags":[2]},{"range":{"start":{"line":263,"character":20},"end":{"line":263,"character":39}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/deprecated"},"source":"deprecated","message":"s.cli.ZRangeByScore is deprecated: Use ZRangeArgs with ByScore option instead as of Redis 6.2.0.","tags":[2]},{"range":{"start":{"line":386,"character":20},"end":{"line":386,"character":44}},"severity":3,"code":"unusedparams","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedparams#unusedparams"},"source":"unusedparams","message":"unused parameter: opts"},{"range":{"start":{"line":398,"character":22},"end":{"line":398,"character":33}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-codin